Frequently Asked Questions about Hyperlipidemia Drugs Market
What is hyperlipidemia?
Hyperlipidemia is a condition characterized by high levels of lipids (fats) in the blood, including cholesterol and triglycerides.

What are hyperlipidemia drugs?
Hyperlipidemia drugs are medications used to lower lipid levels in the blood and reduce the risk of cardiovascular diseases.

